DoS

* Denial of Service

An attempt to make a machine or network resource unavailable to its intended users.

*Symptoms*

- Unusually slow network performance (opening files or accessing web sites)
- Unavailability of a particular web site
- Inability to access any web site
- Dramatic increase in the number of spam emails received (e-mail bomb)
- Disconnection of a wireless or wired internet connection
- Long term denial of access to the web or any internet services

* Attack Techniques

* ICMP Flood

Malformed ICMP packets aimed at consuming targets network and computational resources.

*Smurf*attack*

Intended victim's spoofed source IP are broadcast to a computer network using an IP broadcast address.

*Ping*of*death*

Sending malformed/malicious ping to a computer
e.g. a ping that is bigger than max IPv4 message (65,535 bytes)

*Ping*flood*

Constantly sending pings, without waiting for a response, consuming bandwidth.

* SYN Flood

Sending multiple SYN request to a target's system without responding to ACK, so the target queues them all awaiting a timeout on the request.

